    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@tecmusti Hi! Unfortunately that is not yet possible given the feature of the Algolia REST API. We are currently auto-generating those ranges instead of getting them from the real data.\n\nThus this can sometime lead to bad ranges leading to no results.\n\nYou best option currently would be to use the numericRefinementList that allows you to provide manual values for the ranges along with start/end bounds.\n\nIf you already know what price ranges you want, that's the way to go.\n\nWe will upgrade those numeric ranges widgets soon to make it clearer.\n\nI am gonna update the docuentation to show how to pass manual values to numericRefinementList, in the meantime use this:\n\n``` js\nnumericRefinementList({\n  attributeName: 'price',\n  options: [{\n    name: 'less than 500$',\n    end: 500\n  }]\n})\n```\n\nEtc..\n",
